HEADWORD: Orectic
<hw>O*rec"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'orektiko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>'o`rexis</grk>, yearning after, from
<grk>'ore`gein</grk> to reach after.]</ety> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>Of
or pertaining to the desires; hence, impelling to gratification;
appetitive.</def>⟦br⟧
